### After (O(n) complexity):
```c
for (i = 0; i < g->notifiers_count; i++) {
  if (g->notifiers[i].done == 1 ||
      g->notifiers[i].w != w    ||
      strcmp(g->notifiers[i].notification, notification) != 0)
    continue;  // Skip non-matching or already processed notifiers

  // Process matching notifiers in a single pass
  g->notifiers[i].done = 1;
  handler = g->notifiers[i].handler;
  private = g->notifiers[i].private;
  gunlock(g);
  handler(private, g, notification, w, notification_data);
  glock(g);
}
```

The refactoring maintains all the original behavior:
- Thread safety with proper locking/unlocking
- Handler calls still happen outside the lock to avoid deadlocks
- Notifiers are marked as done to prevent duplicate processing
- The recursive call protection (`inside` static variable) is preserved

